0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: I created "Onward" to honor the people that have contributed, and continue to contribute to the greater goal of an open society. A Cypherpunk's Manifesto was written by Eric Hughes on March 9,1993. It was a declaration and commitment to create technologies that protect our rights of privacy. Eric, David Chaum, Adam Back, Hal Finney, Nick Szabo, and Wei Dai are just a handful of leaders that changed our way of life with their dedication to writing code. Their contributions were the foundations of Satoshi Nakamoto's Bitcoin.   The manifestos last word is onward, which you see the subject in the artwork gazing up towards. She has committed to joining this movement. She wears the bitcoin gas mask as protection from our current world of fiat. At the bottom of the piece you see the date of the manifesto anchoring the artwork. Its a reminder that this journey has been travelled by many before us, and will continue to be travelled by many after us. "Let us proceed together apace. Onward."

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: This is a metaphorical self portrait centering on my spirit of creation, a distinctly female persona who has appeared in my work with green skin and purple hair since 2001. She patiently gestates ideas for long periods of time, refusing to let them go before they're fully developed. Although a man, I have anxious dreams I am pregnant when creative work is ready to finally come into the world and be shared.  She appears naked because I am one of few artists in the #cryptoart space who makes their identity no secret. It feels naked to interact with pseudonyms while as much of my life history is on display as one is interested in learning. Additionally, she resides in the placement of Bartholomew, who was stripped of his skin. Although naked, she appears comfortable, confident, and busy at task.  State 1 : Holding a digital tablet, from which the layers of a dimensional painting spring forward. State 2 : Holding a digital tablet, which features a Processing.org console. "void setup(){} void draw(){}" represents a blank canvas. She pushes a paintbrush over the interface, a literal representation of "painting with code," part of a philosophical approach I take with my work. State 3 : An offset rendering State 4 - 8: Various Wireframe visualizations of the database the figure was saved as.  When she shrinks, you may hardly notice her and forget she is there. But when is full, she is not to be missed.  Exclusive experiences await the token holder: https://collect.mattkane.com/minted-works/first-supper-visionary-spirit-of-creation/

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Faces of Transformation
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The core of the transformation, however, were the insects, which stared at the spectators with their huge fly eyes. Although they tried to hide behind masks and wigs (and thus appear somewhat human-like), they only felt comfortable when they were replaced by an artificially created creature.

But what they seemed to enjoy visibly was the great power to fly around, to change their size and position and thus to question the aesthetics of the whole work.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Holy Tapestry
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The backgrounds takes inspiration from the cypher and cyberpunk imaginary. Some include excerpts from the farsighted works by Timothy C. May (Crypto Anarchist Manifesto, 1988) and Eric Hughes (Cypherpunk Manifesto, 1993), including the following prophetic one:

We the Cypherpunks are dedicated to building anonymous systems. We are defending our privacy with cryptography, with anonymous mail forwarding systems, with digital signatures, and with electronic money. [...] Cypherpunks write code. We know that software can't be destroyed and that a widely dispersed system can't be shut down. Eric Hughes, Cypherpunk Manifesto, 1993

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The prophet's robe

Hence ‘dress’ refers both to the habitat (house) and to what we wear (dress). It also concerns the habits that are a persistent form of our being. And so the Cypher::Prophet dress contains elements of our digital crypto habitat, with references to its cypherpunk origins.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Staff of Cryptopower

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The code tablet
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The classic laptop becomes the tablet of the law, as if to say: everything was already written. On the screen it appears the following citation from The Rape of Lucrece by William Shakespeare:

Time's glory is to calm contending kings
To unmask falsehood, and bring truth to light
To stamp the seal of time in aged things
To wake the morn, and sentinel the night
To wrong the wronger till he render right

As well as this one by Juvenal (Satire VI, lines 347–348, circa 100 A.D.):

But who will guard the guards themselves?

and the original Latin:

Sed quis custodiet ipsos Custodes?

Both citations are contained is the seminal paper of Stuart Haber and Scott Stornetta (How to Time-Stamp a Digital Document, The Journal of Cryptography, 1991) proposing for the very first time the idea of blockchain.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Ends
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
At the 2 ends are the Photographer and the Copper. The photographer sees and feels his photographs, enjoys it and gets obsessed with it. When no one has a chance to give an opinion on his works, to value it or collect it, the photographer himself becomes the admirer. Obsessed in the depths of the meaning of the situation and how it relates to what’s photographed, he himself starts to feel lost, every single day. 
The Copper comes out at night, the bravest of souls, the conquerer of evil, the catcher of thieves. And yet, he is afraid of his own shadow. The shadow which moved synchronously with him, has started to shift and become asynchronous. What does this mean? Does he himself have thievery in him? Is he himself evil?

While the Jeweller adorns himself with an earring, the Reflecter adores himself in his mirror. The Perfumer enjoys his own perfume while the Conner tricks himself into believing. The Soothsayer tries to find what’s his own future is in this uncertainty while the Clother dresses himself in his own fabrics. And at the end of the week, the Sweetmaker, all tired, bites a bit of his own tasty little rasgulla. Where is the world going? Is this what the world is doing to itself? Is the world, through the pandemic, consuming its own creation?

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Hermes Trismegistus
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Ἑρμῆς ὁ Τρισμέγιστος, "thrice-greatest Hermes" is the purported author of the Hermetic Corpus, a series of sacred texts that are the basis of Hermeticism. As a divine source of wisdom, Hermes Trismegistus was credited with tens of thousands of writings of high standing, reputed to be of immense antiquity. The Hermetica is a category of papyri containing spells and initiatory induction procedures. In the dialogue called the Asclepius (after the Greek god of healing) the art of imprisoning the souls of demons or of angels in statues with the help of herbs, gems and odors, is described, such that the statue could speak and engage in prophecy. In other papyri, there are recipes for constructing such images and animating them, such as when images are to be fashioned hollow so as to enclose a magic name inscribed on gold leaf.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Abaris the Hyperborean
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Ἄβαρις Ὑπερβόρειος, son of Seuthes, was a legendary sage, healer, and priest of Apollo known to the Ancient Greeks. He was supposed to have learned his skills in his homeland of Hyperborea, near the Caucasus, which he fled during a plague. He was said to be endowed with the gift of prophecy, and by this as well as by his Scythian dress and simplicity and honesty he created great sensation in Greece, and was held in high esteem.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Aditi of the Kung Paw
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Wind swept through the temple and for a brief moment, the damp smell transported him to the fields as a young kit, chasing mice through cattail and clover by the edge of the Lower Frisk.  Master Aditi suddenly shook his head like a cat in the rain.  Days long gone cannot touch me now.

He bent low over strange clawings on weathered bone, whiskers sweeping dust as the writings unwound their secrets and ancient curses worked into his tongue.  The Emperor had forsaken him and he had wandered the wilderness without honor and without purpose.  Ronin.

As dark spiraling energies rose in his throat, Aditi knew here was a purpose.  Power.  Not political or even physical.  No, here was power at its most raw - the Power of the Breath!  Drawing all his shame and anger, Aditi focused on the rough fibers collecting in his throat, his voice long silenced, his name unspoken.  Let me speak it now!  Kuuuuuuuuuuung PAW!

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Shaolin Sphynx
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
>Orphaned and sold as a pet before escaping to Shao Mountain, the monks of the Temple in the Woods gave refuge to the Sphynx.  Feigning sleep in the day as he watched the monks practice, he copied their moves at night in the dark empty hallways when the fires burned low. 
>After years of training in secret, one moonless night a tiger slipped into the temple undetected by the monks.
>His nose alone sensed the invisible foe, and the Sphynx dropped from the shadows like a wrinkled grey corpse into a tomb - yellow silk pants rippling in the dark, claws and fangs glinting like the bones of his long dead enemies, Feiyue sneakers flashing in firelight.  Two shapes shifted like water under Anji Bridge in winter, shreds of flesh tufted in tigerfur falling like a snowstorm of red and orange burning at sunset.
>When the monks woke in the morning, the Sphynx cat was gone, a tiger shorn and sliced to ribbons lay splayed before the altar, it's eyes wild, wide, and empty. Looking back over his shoulder, Shaolin Sphynx chanted a prayer for his temple brothers and set forth on the high road, called by the rumors of Māo Māo City and a darkness gathering there.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: THE CENTER AND THE CROWD
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: This token contains the entire crowd surrounding the central figure of the artwork, which is included apart from its head. There are 11 different variations, which mainly influence the clothes of the depicted crowd.The only exception is the option "high contrast lunaris", which also changes the skin color. This token influences the atmosphere of the whole work significantly.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: CHOOSE YOUR PROTAGONIST!
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Control the head of the protagonist! Choose your key figure. The entire work revolves around this main character and you can decide who the crowd will gather around. There are 7 different heads to choose from, including 3 well-known personalities from the Blockchain movement: Satoshi Nakamoto, Vitalik Buterin and Nick Szabo. The Cryptonaut stands as an amusing representation from the world of cryptomemes and the head with VR-headset as the central figure of MetaPOP and the emerging METAVERSE movement. DEATH brings the image into more serious realms and the duck head wants to create an absurd and comical atmosphere. CHOOSE YOUR PROTAGONIST!

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: SIGILLUM SANCTORUM
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: The Holy Seal - In what name will the protagonist appear? What significance will the seal have? What crowns the staff of the central figure? -- All this you may decide with the possession of this token. -- 6 different staff tops in total and in different versions.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: MONUMENTA HOMAGE
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: The Monuments of Homage - with this token you control the three Monuments of Homage in different versions. The Unicorn, the Honey Badger and the Holy Gate. While the Unicorn primarily represents all the Blockchain companies that have achieved a certain success and the Honey Badger stands for Bitcoin's fearlessness, the Holy Gate leaves a much greater scope for interpretation. Some rumor it is the "Exit Strategy" and others claim it is the entrance to the rabbit hole of the world of blockchain and crypto currencies. Still others think that the gate stands for the entrance to the METAVERSE. Who knows who's right... The future owner of this token might know the answer.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: DOORS OF PERCEPTION
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: the doors of perception - the elements of this token stand for perception Partly it is predetermined by our biology and psychophysical condition; partly it is determined by the influences of our social environment... in another part we ourselves determine decisively how and what we want to perceive. This token revolves around this symbolism and gives the artwork a special appeal.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: UNICORNIS DE FUTURO...
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: The unicorn from the future... and the breath of life and creation. They both stand for, among other things, future potential, for creativity, for the success of hard work and honest effort. This token lets you choose between different variants or the elements disappear completely.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: SPECULUM TEMPORIS

Let the world know with a tweet or enjoy the changed image in silence, where only you know what is meant.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Puzzle9
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Life is a big puzzle game made up of many different events and experiences, some of which are interrelated and overlap. The more experiences we gather, the more complex and colorful the overall picture becomes.  
 
But over time, the perception, emotional coloring and evaluation of different events and memories changes. Some things we may remember only vaguely after a while. 
 
Thus, the inner thought puzzle of each individual constantly reflects life and yet is greater than the sum of its parts. 
 
The work has been created as part of a conversation with my younger self and the search for my signature style, that I started in July 2020. 
 
It is based on a ballpen drawing from about 1990, that I digitally recreated by accurately following the lines using a graphics drawing tablet. Next I filled the shapes with digital colors before I finally decided to split the work into several puzzle-pieces, that can be independently change hue or alternatively display the outlines to turn it into an interactive AsyncArt work.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: This still-life, titled after one of Pablo Picasso's infamous quotes, was made solely using 3D softwares and apps, in an attempt to bring this often forgotten artistic genre into the 21st century through the use of new artistic mediums and technologies.
